-- K+S Upholds Forecast for De-Icing Salt Amid Warm Winter Weather
-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 2012-01-10T21:04:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/k-s-upholds-forecast-for-de-icing-salt-amid-warm-winter-weather.html
K+S AG, the world’s largest producer
of salt, reiterated a forecast to sell about 14 million metric
tons of de-icing salt this year, after some countries in  Europe 
experienced warmer-than-average winter weather.  Kassel, Germany-based K+S will sell “a good 23 million
tons” of salt this year, about 14 million tons of which will be
de-icing salt, the company said in a  presentation  today.  The U.K. had the mildest December since 2006, according to
the  Met Office . In  Germany , December posted the fifth-warmest
average national temperatures in December since 1881, according
to the  DWD  weather bureau.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
